HEADWORD: Chico
<hw>Chi"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Var. of
<er>Chica</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The common greasewood of the western United States
(<spn>Sarcobatus vermiculatus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In the Philippines, the sapodilla or its fruit;
also, the marmalade tree or its fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chick-pea</ent>⟦br⟧
